%matplotlib ipympl
import ase
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from abtem.bloch import BlochWaves, StructureFactor

import abtem

abtem.config.set(
    {
        "precision": "float64",
        "device": "gpu",
    }
)

<abtem.core.config.set at 0x1adb1da72d0>

atoms = ase.build.bulk("Si", cubic=True)

angle = np.arctan(1/2)

rotated_atoms = atoms.copy()
rotated_atoms.rotate("x", angle * 180 / np.pi, rotate_cell=True)

rotated_atoms.center()

rotated_atoms = abtem.orthogonalize_cell(rotated_atoms)

abtem.show_atoms(rotated_atoms, legend=True, plane="xy")

(<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>, <Axes: xlabel='x [Å]', ylabel='y [Å]'>)

parametrization = abtem.parametrizations.LobatoParametrization(
    sigmas={"Si": 0.078 * np.sqrt(3)}
)

potential = (
    abtem.Potential(
        rotated_atoms,
        sampling=0.02,
        slice_thickness=0.1,
        projection="finite",
        parametrization=parametrization,
    )
    .build()
    .compute(progress_bar=False)
)

potential.shape

(122, 272, 608)

pw = abtem.PlaneWave(energy=200e3)

nz = int(2000 / potential.thickness)

repeated_potential = abtem.CrystalPotential(
    potential, repetitions=[1, 1, nz], exit_planes=potential.num_slices
)

exit_waves_ms = pw.multislice(potential=repeated_potential).compute()

[########################################] | 100% Completed | 20.21 s

from abtem.atoms import euler_to_rotation

orientation_matrices = euler_to_rotation(angle, 0, 0, axes="xzx")

diffraction_ms = (
    exit_waves_ms.diffraction_patterns()
    .to_cpu()
    .crop(200)
    .index_diffraction_spots(
        cell=atoms, orientation_matrices=orientation_matrices, centering="F"
    )
    .compute()
)

# diffraction_ms[-1].block_direct().crop(100).show(
#    scale=0.05, annotations=True, interact=True
# )

sg_max = 0.4
k_max = 18

structure_factor = StructureFactor(
    atoms, k_max=k_max, parametrization="lobato", centering="F", thermal_sigma=0.078
)

bloch_waves = BlochWaves(
    structure_factor=structure_factor, energy=200e3, sg_max=sg_max, paraxial=True
)

len(bloch_waves)

8203

rotated = bloch_waves.rotate("x", angle)

diffraction_bw = (
    rotated.calculate_diffraction_patterns(
        thicknesses=repeated_potential.exit_thicknesses
    )
    .compute()
    .to_cpu()
    .crop(200)
)

exit_waves_bw = rotated.calculate_exit_wave(
    repeated_potential.exit_thicknesses,
    gpts=exit_waves_ms.gpts,
    extent=exit_waves_ms.extent,
)

diffraction_bw_2 = (
    exit_waves_bw.diffraction_patterns()
    .to_cpu()
    .crop(200)
    .index_diffraction_spots(
        cell=atoms, orientation_matrices=orientation_matrices, centering="F"
    )
    .compute()
)

# diffraction_bw[0, -1].block_direct().crop(200).show(scale=0.05, annotations=True, interact=True)

stack = abtem.stack(
    [diffraction_ms, diffraction_bw, diffraction_bw_2],
    axis_metadata={"label": "algorithm", "values": ["MS", "BW", "BW2"]},
    axis=1,
)

data = stack.to_data_array()

data = data.sel(hkl=(data.max("z") > 1e-6).any("algorithm"))

r = np.abs(np.sqrt(data[:, 0]) - np.sqrt(data[:, 1:])).sum("hkl") / np.abs(
    np.sqrt(data[:, 0])
).sum("hkl") * 100

r = r.rolling(z=3).mean()

plt.figure()
r.plot.line(hue="algorithm")

[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x1b013d6c110>,
 <matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x1b013d6fa10>]

plt.figure()
data.sel(hkl="4 0 0").plot.line(hue="algorithm")
